NAME
ORPGCFG_dataid_to_path - given a datastore data ID, return the
    corresponding system configuration datastore path

SYNOPSIS
#include <orpgcfg.h>

const char *
ORPGCFG_dataid_to_path(int data_id, const char *syscfg_fname)


DESCRIPTION
ORPGCFG_dataid_to_path returns the system configuration pathname for
the datastore corresponding to the specified data ID.

"data_id" must correspond to a valid data ID.

If the system configuration filename "syscfg_fname" is either a NULL
pointer or points to an empty string, the default system configuration
file will be searched.  Otherwise, the specified system configuration
file (assumed to be a Configuration Support-style file) will be searched.

RETURNS
ORPGCFG_dataid_to_path returns a pointer to the (null-terminated)
datastore path upon success; otherwise, a pointer to an empty string
is returned.

NOTES
ORPGCFG_dataid_to_path has the side-effect of resetting the current
CS configuration file to the default system configuration file.

This function may return a pointer to static storage that may then
be overwritten by a subsequent call to this function.

